data.enText: to say or do sth that offends sb

data.chText: 我一生中从未被如此侮辱过！
data.enText: I have never been so insulted in my life!

data.chText: 那么低的出价使她觉得受到了侮辱。
data.enText: She felt insulted by the low offer.
a remark or an action that is said or done in order to offend sb
The crowd were shouting insults at the police.

data.chText: 他的评论被看成是对主席的冒犯。
data.enText: His comments were seen as an insult to the president.

data.chText: 那些问题（简单得）有辱我们的智慧。
data.enText: The questions were an insult to our intelligence (= too easy) .

data.chText: 伤害之余又侮辱（使原本不好的关系更加恶化）
data.enText: to make a bad relationship with sb worse by offending them even more

simple_means.memory_skill: in 使… + sult 跳 → 使跳到〔别人脸上〕→ 侮辱〔别人〕

data.chText: 伤害之余又侮辱（使原本不好的关系更加恶化）
data.enText: to make a bad relationship with sb worse by offending them even more

tr: a deliberately offensive act or something producing the effect of deliberate disrespect
example: turning his back on me was a deliberate insult

tr: a rude expression intended to offend or hurt
example: when a student made a stupid mistake he spared them no abuse
they yelled insults at the visiting team

tr: treat, mention, or speak to rudely
example: He insulted her with his rude remarks
the student who had betrayed his classmate was dissed by everyone

value.boxr_value: The verb is pronounced /ɪn'sʌlt/. The noun is pronounced /'ɪnsʌlt/. 动词读作 /ɪn'sʌlt/。名词读作 /'ɪnsʌlt/。

value.def: If someone insults you, they say or do something that is rude or offensive.

example.ex: I did not mean to insult you...
Buchanan said he was insulted by the judge's remarks.
example.tran: 布坎南说法官的那番话侮辱了他。

example.ex: I would be a bit insulted if he said anything like that.
example.tran: 如果他说过任何那样的话,我会感到有些受辱的。

value.def: An insult is a rude remark, or something a person says or does which insults you.

example.ex: Their behaviour was an insult to the people they represent...
example.tran: 他们的行为是对他们代表的人民的一种侮辱。

example.ex: The prison Governor criticised some of his officers who shouted insults at prisoners on the roof.
example.tran: 监狱长批评了一些站在屋顶上大声辱骂囚犯的狱警。

value.def: You say to add insult to injury when mentioning an action or fact that makes an unfair or unacceptable situation even worse.

example.ex: The driver of the car that killed Smith got a £250 fine and five penalty points on his licence. To add insult to injury, he drove away from court in his own car.
example.tran: 撞死史密斯的汽车司机仅被罚款250英镑，驾照上扣了5分。更让人不可接受的是,他竟然开着自己的车从法院扬长而去。

value.tran: 更为不公的是;更不可接受的是;更糟的是
